The IUCN classifies endangered species into six categories: "potentially endangered" to "endangered", "highly endangered", "threatened to extinction" and "extinct in the wild" to "extinct". In total, it lists more than 28,000 animal and plant species as endangered worldwide.
Eberish and wild Roskastania threatened
