Aegean: Baby and four other children drowned in a boat accident
A baby and four other children drowned while anchoring a refugee boat in the Aegean Sea, killing seven people in total, the Greek coast guard said on Friday.
The boat sank near the Greek island of Inousses, which lies between the island of Chios and the Turkish mainland.
Hundreds of migrants are now crossing from Turkey to the Greek islands in the eastern Aegean Sea, where 174 people died last year, according to the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR).
